Title: Characterizing SERCA Function in Murine Skeletal Muscles after 35-37 Days of Spaceflight from RR-1 and RR-9 (calcium uptake and Western blot in soleus and tibialis anterior)

Organism: Mouse

Mission: SpaceX-12, SpaceX-4

This dataset was funded by Brock University and the Canada Research Chair Tier II in Tissue Plasticity and Remodelling Throughout the Lifespan.

URI and contents are provided below:

https://nasa-ames-data-archive.github.io/OSD-488/

Contains data on SERCA function in mice after 35-37 days of spaceflight. The dataset includes protocols for animal husbandry, sample collection, reaction mixture information, plating information, kinetic read information, ALSDA transformed data, protein gel info, protein blot transfer info, blocking protocol, labeling information, and western blot imaging and quantification.

This dataset is suitable for researchers studying the effects of spaceflight on muscle function and regulation.
